<div class="row">
	<ol class="breadcrumb">
  		<li><h3><a href="#">SalesHub</a></h3></li>
  		<li class="active"><small>Leads</small></li>
	</ol>
</div>

<p>En cliquant sur les entetes de colonne, on classe par ordre croissant ou décroissant.
</p>
<p> <div ng-show="predicate == ''"> Actuellement la liste n'est pas classée</div></p>
<p><a href="" ng-show="predicate != ''" ng-click="predicate=''">Annuler le classement</a></p>

<table class="table table-striped table-bordered table-hover" >
    				<thead>
    					<tr>
    					<th ng-click="orderBy('lastname')">nom</th>
    					<th ng-click="orderBy('firstname')">prénom</th>
    					<th ng-click="orderBy('email')">email</th>
    					<th ng-click="orderBy('phone')">téléphone</th>
    					<th>Propales</tr>
    					<tr>
    				</thead>
    				<tbody>
    					
    					{% verbatim %}
    					<tr ng-repeat="employee in employees | orderBy:predicate:reverse">
    						<td><strong>{{ employee.lastname }}</strong></td>
    						<td>{{ employee.firstname }}</td>
    						<td><a href="mailto:{{ employee.email }}">{{ employee.email }}</a></td>
    						<td>{{ employee.phone }}</td>
    						<td ng-click="goOrdo()">{{ employee.proposal }}</td>
    					</tr>
    					{% endverbatim %}
    					
    				</tbody>
    			</table>
    			

